  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2083",
  "title": "[Feature] Add option to open collapsible based on isRefined",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nSometimes a refinement list might be collapsed by default, but if it has been refined and the user reloads the page, it would be nice to have it opened instead of collapsed.\r\n\r\n![issue with collapsible refined](https://cl.ly/003T3V023G2r/Screen%20Recording%202017-03-29%20at%2006.17%20PM.gif)\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your proposed API entry? The new option to add? What is the behavior?**\r\nAdd a property in the `collapsible` object, like `collapsedIfRefined` with a boolean value (default `true` to not change existing behavior).\r\nExpected usage based on current options would be something like this:\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    ...\r\n    collapsible: {\r\n      collapsed: true,\r\n      collapsedIfRefined: false\r\n    }\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- instantsearch.js\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nLatest\r\n",
